* {{IPA|/ˈdɛ.nɪ.ɡɹeɪt/|lang=en}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|dēnigrātus}}, the past participle of {{m|la|dēnigrāre||to blacken}}, from {{m|la|dē}} + [[nigrare]] 'to blacken (from {{term|niger||black|lang=la}})

===Verb===
{{en-verb|denigrat|ing}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[criticise]] so as to [[besmirch]]; [[traduce]], [[disparage]] or [[defame]].
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To treat as [[worthless]]; [[belittle]], [[degrade]] or [[disparage]].
# {{context|rare|lang=en}} To [[blacken]]. <!-- this usage is the literal sense, yet obscure at best -->

